AWS Signature Version 4 known-answer test vectors
-------------------------------------------------
The SigV4 request-signing implementations used by the AWS providers
(Amazon Bedrock LLM, Amazon Transcribe STT, Amazon Polly TTS) are hand-rolled
over `reqwest` + HMAC-SHA256 / SHA-256 — no AWS SDK is used. Their unit tests
pin correctness against the AWS-published SigV4 known-answer test vectors
(the "Examples of signing AWS requests with Signature Version 4" /
GET-vanilla derivation vectors). Those vectors are published by Amazon Web
Services in the AWS General Reference documentation.

    Amazon Web Services SigV4 signing examples
    (C) Amazon Web Services, Inc. — used as published reference test vectors.
    https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/sigv4-signed-request-examples.html

Provider wire protocols
-----------------------
Flowcat speaks the network wire protocols of third-party speech, language, and
telephony vendors (e.g. Google Gemini Live, OpenAI / OpenAI-Realtime, Anthropic,
Deepgram, Cartesia, ElevenLabs, AssemblyAI, Twilio / Telnyx / Plivo / Vonage and
the other serializers, etc.). Those protocols, API schemas, service names, and
trademarks are the property of their respective owners. Flowcat is an independent
client implementation and is not endorsed by or affiliated with any of these
vendors. Use of any provider requires the user's own credentials and acceptance
of that vendor's terms.

